Nairobi governor candidate Miguna Miguna on Friday said his choice of James Githungu, 24, as running mate was a decoy.&ldquo;... to throw my opponents off the balance. You know there are many cartels and Miguna is a strategist,&rdquo; he said.Miguna dropped Githungu for businesswoman Karen Wangenye. He spoke after he received his clearance certificate from the IEBC. Miguna was turned back on Thursday after he submitted a list of 500 signatures in JPEG format. He brought it back in Excel format as asked but was not given a certificate because he did not submit a campaign schedule.On Friday he finally received his certificate. Miguna attacked his opponents, saying they are not fit to run for the seat.